ription": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2022-08-14T07:14:46Z", "updated_at": "2022-10-25T03:11:42Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "On Windows 11 when linking a `dylib` which uses `XInput1_4.dll` using `rust-lld` the compiled binary will crash will a message: `STATUS_STACK_BUFFER_OVERRUN`.\r\n\r\nThis issue was originally reported on Bevy project: https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/issues/2921\r\n\r\nHere is a minimal example that reproduces the error: https://github.com/afonsolage/xinput_link_example\r\n```\r\nerror: process didn't exit successfully: `target\\debug\\xinput_link_example.exe` (exit code: 0xc0000409, STATUS_STACK_BUFFER_OVERRUN)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error won't happens when using MSVC `link.exe` \r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.65.0-nightly (75b7e52e9 2022-08-13)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: 75b7e52e92c3b00fc891b47f5b2efdff0a2be55a\r\nrelease: 1.65.0-nightly\r\nLLVM version: 15.0.0\r\n```\r\n\r\nWindows version:\r\n```\r\nEdition:\tWindows 11 Home Single Language\r\nVersion:\t22H2\r\nInstalled:\t\u200e16/\u200e07/\u200e2022\r\nOS Build:\t22622.575\r\nExperience:\tWindows Feature Experience Pack 1000.22634.1000.0\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/100519/reactions", "total_count": 10, "+1": 10, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/100519/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}